 {"id":"bd-h0860","title":"PORT: secure_path (NetBSD libutil security check)","description":"Port the NetBSD libutil `secure_path(path)` security check used by inetd, getty, login, and other daemons to verify that a referenced configuration file or executable is owned by root and not group- or world-writable. Returns 0 if the path passes (stat succeeds, st_uid == 0, S_IWGRP and S_IWOTH bits both clear). Returns -1 on any failure (stat fails, owned by non-root, writable by non-owner) with errno set to EPERM (or the underlying stat errno). Implementation: thin abi shim using existing stat() machinery; no core code needed since the logic is just stat+bit-test. Tests: secure path passes; non-root-owned path fails (use temp file owned by current user when not root); world-writable path fails (chmod 666); group-writable fails (chmod 660 with non-root group); nonexistent path fails with the underlying stat errno; NULL path returns -1 EFAULT or similar.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T09:36:53.524266733Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T09:41:13.701857525Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T09:41:13.699799538Z","close_reason":"shipped: secure_path with lstat + uid/mode bit-tests + 6 abi tests covering NULL/nonexistent/world-writable/group-writable/non-root-owned/secure passing, all green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
